<bibRefCitation author="Krapovickas, A." box="[326,536,230,257]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="5 - 45" refId="ref19451" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2006) Las especies argentinas y de paises vecinos de Sida secc. Nelavaga (Malvaceae, Malveae). Bonplandia 15: 5 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 151 - 289" type="journal article" year="2006">Krapovickas 2006</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodrigo" authorityYear="1937" box="[553,716,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradoxa">
<emphasis box="[553,716,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida paradoxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the other species of Sect. 
<emphasis box="[1295,1451,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Malacroideae</emphasis>
of 
<collectingRegion box="[170,392,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1825" box="[407,566,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anomala">
<emphasis box="[407,566,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida anomala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the cuneate-truncate leaf blades, subentire, with three teeth at the apex; flowers 
<quantity box="[228,306,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" unit="cm" value="2.5">2.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter; fruits with 5 mericarps (vs. linear leaf blades, serrate in the upper half; flowers 
<quantity box="[1365,1421,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
in diameter; fruits with 7–8 mericarps). In the present work, photos of the species in its habitat are presented for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="119" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,158,653]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,763,410,436]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodrigo" authorityYear="1937" box="[791,962,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradoxa">
<emphasis box="[791,962,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida paradoxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[1099,1210,410,436]" name="Argentina" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(only in 
<collectingRegion country="Argentina" name="Corrientes" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Corrientes province</collectingRegion>
) and in 
<collectingCountry box="[328,399,446,472]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, only in state of 
<collectingRegion box="[586,796,446,472]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Krapovickas, A." box="[812,1021,446,473]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="292 - 333" refId="ref19401" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2005) Malvaceae. In: Bacigalupo, N. M. (Ed.) Flora Ilustrada de Entre-Rios. 6 (4 b). Colecc. Ci. Inst. Nac. Tecnol. Agropecu, pp. 292 - 333." type="book chapter" year="2005">Krapovickas 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[1033,1255,446,472]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis box="[1132,1189,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bovini, M. G." box="[1266,1410,446,472]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
), in Park grassland (
<figureCitation box="[317,417,482,509]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="12.[136,229,2030,2052]" captionTargetBox="[315,1294,482,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-118@12.[258,1329,425,2006]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution map of Sida glaziovii, S. paradoxa, S. linifolia, S. nemorensis, S. planicaulis, S. potentilloides and S. rubifolia in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415497/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Figure 5</figureCitation>
). With the available records, the species presents an EOO of 46,921.776 Km² and an AOO of 100 Km². The species is here considered Endangered (EN), criterion B2b(i, ii, iii)c(i, ii), due to the continuous reduction observed in its habitat and its area of occupancy (
<bibRefCitation author="Mapbiomas" box="[801,1003,554,580]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" refId="ref19791" refString="Mapbiomas (2020) Available from: https: // mapbiomas. org / (accessed 24 November 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Mapbiomas 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
